description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Organisational Development Practitioner &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 position (flexible allocation of 3 days (22.5 hours))&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity for an experienced Organisational Development Practitioner to join our Organisational Development (OD) Team based at University Hospitals Coventry &amp; Warwickshire NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be joining a small team in the Transformation Directorate who are committed to delivering the Trust’s OD priorities that support the Trust’s vision to be a leading healthcare provider and employer, both nationally and internationally. Working with a consultancy and project management approach the successful candidate will be collaborating with team members to design, develop, implement and evaluate organisational development interventions at the individual, team and organisational level. Some areas of focus for this role will include employee engagement, culture transformation and team development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will suit a confident, proactive, hands-on and collaborative individual who enjoys establishing relationships at all levels of the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the OD Team, the successful candidate will be working in a team where continued personal development is valued and encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications close on midnight 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assessment center will be held on 1st December 2020&lt;/strong&gt; please ensure you are available on this date should your application be short listed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To arrange an informal discussion about this role, please contact – Rajni Martin, Organisational Development Manager by email Rajni.martin@uhcw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal discussion about this role, please contact – Rajni Martin or Michelle Brookhouse on 02476 968665&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
